BULAWAYO lawyer Mr Thandazani Masiye-Moyo has been elected as the new Law Society of Zimbabwe (LSZ) president, taking over from Mr Misheck Hogwe, whose tenure had expired. Mr Masiye- Moyo, a senior partner at Masiye-Moyo and Associates Legal Practitioners in Bulawayo was a councillor at the LSZ prior to his elevation to head the organisation. He will be deputised by Mr Tatenda Mawere of Mawere, Sibanda Commercial Lawyers. More to follow. . .